      • nextSiblingNode

      • isBetween

        public boolean isBetween(Node startNode,
                         Node endNode)
        Whether or not this node occurs in the range between the specified startNode and endNode, inclusive of the start and end nodes.
        Parameters:
        startNode - lower bound node, or null for no lower bound.
        endNode - upper bound node, or null for no upper bound.

      • isBetween

        public boolean isBetween(Node startNode,
                         Node endNode,
                         boolean inclusive)
        Whether or not this node occurs in the range between the specified startNode and endNode, inclusivity as specified.
        Parameters:
        startNode - lower bound node, or null for no lower bound.
        endNode - upper bound node, or null for no upper bound.
        inclusive - whether the range is inclusive of the startNode and endNode.
